0.3 “Affiliate” means any entity that directly or indirectly controls, is
controlled by, or is under common control with a party, where “control” means
ownership of more than 50% of the voting interests or the ability to direct the
management of the entity.

0.4 “Use” means to install, execute, load, run, or otherwise make the Software
function for Licensee’s internal purposes.

0.5 “Modification” means any change to the Software, including derivative works,
adaptations, bug fixes, patches or improvements.

0.6 “Non‑Production Use” means Use solely for research, evaluation, academic
work, experimentation, prototyping, or development, not providing outputs or
services to third parties for a fee or as part of Licensee’s production
workloads.

0.7 “Production Use” means Use in or for Licensee’s products, customer‑facing
services, internal production workloads, or any commercial deployment, whether
or not for direct fee.

0.8 “Contribution” means any code, documentation, or other material intentionally
submitted by Licensee to the public Mol‑Rep‑Haskell‑Bayes repository (e.g., via
